<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-073-718  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 073 718.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Digital Review  Jan 22 1990 v7 n3 p25(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Ziff-Davis Publishing Co. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Data channel converts parallel buses to serial. (Optical DataChannel 11 from Pacific Computer Sales) (product announcement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Bowen, Ted Smalley.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Pacific Computer Sales Inc. (product introduction).andO;Product:   Pacific Computer Sales Optical Data Channel 11 (computercommunications equipment) (product introduction).andO;Topic:     Product IntroductionData CommunicationsFiber OpticsCommunications EquipmentI-O Devices.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>Data Channel Converts Paralel Buses to SerialandM;BOISE, Idaho -- Pacific Computer Sales has deveoped an optical data channelthat converts DEC's DRV11 and DR11 parallel buses to serial lines andincreases the lines' operating distance to 700 meters.andM;The Optical Data Channel 11 (ODC-11) consists of two AMD TAXImicroprocessors, one each for transmission and reception of data; atransistor-to-transistor logic interface to the DRV11/DR11 bus; and aninterface to the analog circuitry, according to Carl Boehme, PacificComputer's president.andM;Uses Fiber-Optic CableandM;&quot;We had the ability to use coax cable, but it only provides an operatingdistance of 240 feet,&quot; Boehme said.andM;The converter uses fiber-optic cable &quot;to eliminate the 40 parallel linesrequired to carry the signal, as a continuation of the electrical interval,and also to provide immunity [from electromagnetic interference},&quot; Boehmesaid.andM;DEC produces a long-line hardwire parallel interface that has a range of1,000 feet.andM;&quot;The ODC-11 is a general purpose in that you can convert any parallel channelto [a] serial [channel],&quot; Boehme said.andM;The ODC-11's AMD TAXI chip set, derived from the FDDI chip set, convertsparallel data to and from the DRV11/DR11 at 120 Mbits per second, accordingto Boehme.andP;  The data is then transmitted and received over fiber-optic cable.andM;&quot;The TAXI chip set can only serve a single destination, without additionalprotocols, but you have the physical side of the FDDI protocol,&quot; Boehme said.andM;Data transmission on the serial connection is duplex and makes use of theFDDI 4B/5B encoding convention, according to Boehme.andP;  The packages consist of6 bytes: 2 control, 2 data, 1 cyclic redundancy check and 1 synchronous,Boehme said.andM;The ODC-11 requires 50 watts of power.andM;It will be available in March and is priced at $4,995.andM;For more information, Pacific Computer Sales Inc. can be contacted at 240 S.andO;Cole Road, Boise, ID 89709, (208) 322-1112.andO;</TEXT></DOC>